76561198004957814,Recommended,249570,8971734,"Posted: 4 February, 2014",all,Krimes,"After abit of poking from friends (a big thank you too Yorkie & Griff) i decided to get past the basic graphics and give this a go.I must say I had been intrigued by the concept from the start and if your totaly honest with yourself it appeals too our dark side of griefing other players.there is no team work co-operation bargining trading guilds leagues ..... its just you, oh and the loving wife and kids. Who strangely dont seem to matter as much as your money when your robbed. I've watched many a UTube vid where father arrives home and the missus and kids have been brutely executed in all the glorious 8bit detail and he casualy walks past their corpses lamanting about the money he has just lost and thinking of how he can upgrade his security. Life goes on I guess.The game is deceptively simple to learn but hard to master. I had a good understanding of what needed to be done within half an hour but then I found myself working on my house for the next 3 hours trying to get the right balance of false sense of security for anyone wishing to come into my welcoming home and death around every corner for said person once hes taken 10 steps. Then theres the carrot, sure you could spend your $2000.00 starting cash on everything barring the kitchen sink (please note there are actualy no kitchen sinks in the game at this time) but whos going to try and rob you if their risking death for 3 bucks. That $2000.00 start up money isn't looking as generous as it did 10 seconds ago is it.Happy with my death house from hell with a nice little carrot of $638.00 I headed out to partake in the second part of the game robbing everyone else blind. So after taking 11 steps into my first house ready to rob the rich and give to the poor, namely me, I found my self well and truly screwed. All I can say Mr Francis Dukis' wont have to feed that pitbull for a week due to the abundance of my carcess it threw around the place.I had just discoverd the joys of my first permadeath! House gone , Wife and Kids gone (probably went off and married pitbull Dukis') my money gone and 3 HOURS of REAL LIFE GONE!!!. So back i went to my new life and started all over vowing to never die again ... yea right.Overall this game is very promising the concept is fantastic and dark. I would like to think they will expand the crimes you can commit with the end result a dystopian society like in the movie ""The Purge"". If you do not know what this movie is google is your friend.No doubt there are a lot of traps and equipment to be added to the game but from what i've read the developers are extremily commited to the game wanting the finished product to give the best possible gaming experience to us, the guys who pay the bills.If I had one grip it would be that there needs to be something implemented sooner than later so you actually care what happens to your family instead of them just being cannon fodder.I feel the game is a solid 7 out of 10 at this stage of development.So get past the 8bit graphics (I did) and buy this game you wont regret it, it is only going to improve from here.Now if you'll excuse me I must go and have a meet and greet with my new family ....... goddamn permadeath."
