,Recommended,249570,18420366,"Posted: 10 October, 2015",all,ChildClownOutlet,"The most physiologically demanding game of all time.  I felt these emotions/effects in games before: adrenaline, fear, being in the zone, pressure, and exuberance.  But Castle Doctrine transcends what it means to 'feel' in a game.  Putting aside the awesome security/reward/strategy/defense/math aspects, this game will make your heart race.  After grinding and amassing a fortune, you can spend hours designing and fortifying your house, only to lose it all after a simple mis-wiring or off-by-one timing of a trap.  And all this, you repeat in your head, you brought upon yourself.  The permadeath without fanfare is the most humbling experience in games.  One second, you are top of the world.  The next, you stare at your screen in jaw-dropped horror, realizing you are trapped in a dead end because you forgot to remove a wall or your wiring connected power to the powered-door directly.This game needs a warning attached:  MAY CAUSE CARDIAC PROBLEMS.I give Jason Rohrer  ""2014 Game of the Year"" for this gem.   I will make a remake of this game in the future.  Will never forget it.As of 10/2015, sadly there are only a handful of players.  When this game had 200+, it was amazing.  Although even today, it still has replay value somehow."
