76561198128470731,Not Recommended,249570,18274117,"Posted: 1 October, 2015",all,Redless,"If you've made it this far you know that the concept for this game is really, really good. Unfortunately, the execution is mind blowingly bad. First and foremost of the problems is the fact that you have to completely rebuild your house after each death, and you cannot go to other houses without doing this. As a result the game will be building house setup, dying to another setup, rebuilding house, over and over again, each time manually. This gets old very quickly.Another issue the game has is its learning curve. It is a very brutal game to learn. This compounds the first problem.Balance in the game is not stellar. Since each profile can only have one house set up at a time, it becomes impossible to test out new traps without demolishing your current house. In addition, the one-house setup encourages folk to just camp out once they have a nice house built, and not go into other homes. They have nothing to gain and everything to lose.Now imagine none of those problems exist. The game is still bad because it is an mmo built around player interaction and almost no one plays it, ever."
