76561197960436733,Recommended,249570,8930859,"Posted: 31 January, 2014",all,PsiShock101,"So I picked up a game called The Castle Doctrine (Named loosely after the same law). The concept is simple, use $2000 to design a trap-ridden puzzle house that protects your vault and your family while providing a completely unhindered exit. You play against people who enter with 2 problems, 1. Death if they hit a trap and 2. If they leave, they drop their backpack containing all of their stupid expensive burglary tools. You can do the same to others. The idea is to design a home that shows opportunity, for example, a small search area, while being defended enough to prevent someone from casing the place then coming back with appropriate equipment. It's a lot of fun. Not quite worth the $15 ( Got it on sale) yet because it is a kickstarter game it's incomplete. But it is functional and is too simple to have many bugs. Very interesting game all around but anyone who requires graphics and 3D will not want to play. 7/10"
